  "texts": [
    "In contrast, algorithm-level strategies introduce targeted solutions to class imbalance without altering the underlying data distribution.",
    "They exhibit an advantage in that they are less likely to affect training time, yet they demand an in-depth understanding of the algorithm in use and are inherently algorithm-specific, potentially compromising their flexibility and ease of implementation.",
    "CSL stands out for its computational efficiency and data distribution preservation while addressing class imbalance.",
    "Nonetheless, it presents challenges in setting appropriate misclassification costs, often requiring careful optimisation and facing potential overfitting to the minority class during cost tuning.",
    "Note that a detailed exposition of the strengths and weaknesses associated with CSL is provided in Subsection 6.1."
  ],
